  "text": "To the best of our knowledge, this is the first analysis of differential gene expression following infection with a torovirus. It would be of interest to repeat this analysis at later time points, as a previous study found that EToV-mediated global inhibition of host protein synthesis was only detectable at 16 h postinfection (h.p.i.). The same study found induction of both the intrinsic and extrinsic apoptotic pathways was evident only by 24 h.p.i. [CITATION_1] . It is clear that the transcriptional and translational profile of the host cell may differ significantly throughout the course of infection. Additionally, it must be noted that the horse (Equus caballus) genome is not highly annotated, and thus many Ensembl gene identifications do not possess an annotated orthologue, a limiting factor in our analysis.",
